8 person-info-wrapper\">\n\n\t\t\t<div class=\"profile-container summary\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<p>Dwaine specializes in the integration of art and design. His architecture has received numerous awards and is published in <em>The Architects Newspaper</em>, <em>Architectural Record</em>, <em>Sunset</em>, <em>How</em>, and <em>Sun Valley Art</em> magazines and most recently featured in the University of Washington Press book, <em>Daylight Design in the Pacific Northwest</em>.</p>\n<p>As an artist and cultural planner, Dwaine has created and exhibited work throughout the region. His works range from the Arts Master Plan for Boise Public Works Watershed Education Center to permanent public artworks such as Boise City Hall's \"Cottonwoods,\" \u201cHistoric Sight: Boise Chinatown\u201d and \u201cHeliotrope.\u201d His work is distinguished by numerous grant and competition awards as well as installations and exhibits at Sun Valley Center for the Arts and Humanities, the Visual Arts Center at Boise State University, J Crist Gallery, and Rhode Island School of Design.</p>\n<p>Dwaine is a graduate of Harvard University and holds Fine Arts and Architecture degrees from Rhode Island School of Design. He is a developed communicator committed to open, creative processes. He combines his interpretive abilities with sensitivity to site, materials and concepts that enable the collaborative creation of outstanding environments and experiences. He has been a guest critic at numerous institutions including Rhode Island School of Design, University of Pennsylvania and the Graduate School of Design at Harvard University.</p>\n\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t<div class=\"profile-container education\">\n            <p><a href=\"/caa\">College of Art and Architecture</a></p>\n\n            <p><a href=\"/caa/programs/architecture\">Architecture</a></p>\n\t\t</div>\n\n\t</div>\n\n\t<div class=\"col-sm-12 col-lg-4 pull-left-sm pull-right-lg clear-right-lg optional-content-wrapper\">\n\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"links profile-container-optional-content\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<h4>Courses</h4>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<hr>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<ul>\n    <li>ARCH 204: ST: Intro to Des. in Built Env</li>\n    <li>ARCH 510: Graduate Project Seminar</li>\n</ul>\n\t\t\t\t\t</div>\n\t</div>\n</div>"}
