 style=\"letter-spacing: -0.9pt;\"> </span>his<span style=\"letter-spacing: -0.9pt;\"> </span>PhD<span style=\"letter-spacing: -0.7pt;\"> </span>in<span style=\"letter-spacing: 0.3pt;\"> </span>General<span style=\"letter-spacing: -0.5pt;\"> </span>Experimental<span style=\"letter-spacing: -0.1pt;\"> </span>Psychology,<span style=\"letter-spacing: -0.05pt;\"> </span>he<span style=\"letter-spacing: -0.5pt;\"> </span>became<span style=\"letter-spacing: 0.1pt;\"> </span>a<span style=\"letter-spacing: -1.1pt;\"> </span>post-doctoral<span style=\"letter-spacing: -0.1pt;\"> </span>fellow<span style=\"letter-spacing: -0.1pt;\"> </span>at the Institute of Child Development at the University of Minnesota. In <span style=\"letter-spacing: 0.1pt;\">1971 he </span>came to the University of Idaho and taught all the developmental courses for 28 <span style=\"letter-spacing: -0.15pt;\">years</span></span><span style=\"color: #383838; letter-spacing: -0.15pt;\">. </span><span style=\"color: #181818;\">Starting with the second WWAMI class in 1974 he taught behavioral medicine until 2012. He is a veteran and continues to live in Moscow<span style=\"letter-spacing: -0.3pt;\"> </span>with<span style=\"letter-spacing: -0.8pt;\"> </span>his<span style=\"letter-spacing: -0.65pt;\"> </span>wife<span style=\"letter-spacing: -0.95pt;\"> </span>Charlott<span style=\"letter-spacing: 0.3pt;\">e</span></span><span style=\"color: #383838; letter-spacing: 0.3pt;\">. He is the original Dr. Phil. </span></p>\n<p>\u00a0</p>\n\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t<div class=\"profile-container education\">\n            <p><a href=\"/class\">College of Letters, Arts and Social Sciences</a></p>\n\n            <p><a href=\"/class/psychcomm\">Psychology and Communication Studies Department</a></p>\n\t\t</div>\n\n\t</div>\n\n\t<div class=\"col-sm-12 col-lg-4 pull-left-sm pull-right-lg clear-right-lg optional-content-wrapper\">\n\n\t</div>\n</div>"}
